The paper deals with privacy definitions and algorithms for protecting sensitive data, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses Bayesian inference and convex sets, which are topics related to machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). Information theory (cs.IT) is also relevant to the paper's focus on privacy guarantees. Finally, the paper discusses algorithms that add noise to data, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
